Police safely destroy car bomb in Spain . Spanish police said on Tuesday they safely destroyed a bomb planted in a prison worker ' s car in the southern city of Granada . The prison worker , identified only as the father of two young children , alerted police who then carried out a controlled explosion . Officials did not say whether Basque separatist rebels ETA were responsible , but the group has targeted prison staff over the past year and the device was made of materials ETA ( Basque Homeland and Freedom ) has used in its drive for independence . ETA , which has held a prison worker hostage for more than 500 days , claimed responsibility for killing a prison psychologist on March 11 . 
